---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About PKD Cure Tracker — our mission to provide impartial, up-to-date information on PKD research for patients and caregivers.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">About PKD Cure Tracker</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
      <p class="text-lg">
        PKD Cure Tracker is an informational website built for patients, caregivers, and the broader PKD community. Our mission is simple: deliver the latest research, clinical trial updates, and treatment developments as soon as the information becomes available.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-4">Why this exists</h2>
      <p>
        Research into Polycystic Kidney Disease is moving faster than ever. New drugs are entering clinical trials, ketogenic interventions are showing real results, and the pace of published studies continues to accelerate. But keeping up with all of it is hard — information is scattered across academic journals, government databases, conference proceedings, and Facebook groups.
      </p>
      <p>
        PKD Cure Tracker exists to solve that problem. We aggregate, organize, and present the information in a way that's quick to navigate and easy to understand, so you can stay informed without spending hours digging through sources.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-4">Our principles</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Impartial information</strong> — We present the data and research as it is, without bias toward any particular treatment or commercial interest.</li>
        <li><strong>100% free, 100% ad-free</strong> — This website has no ads, no paywalls, and no sponsorships. It will stay that way.</li>
        <li><strong>Speed</strong> — When new information comes out, we aim to have it on the site as quickly as possible.</li>
        <li><strong>Community-driven</strong> — This project exists for the PKD community and grows with its input and collaboration.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-4">Who it's for</h2>
      <p>
        Whether you're a patient recently diagnosed, a long-time caregiver, a family member trying to understand the landscape, or a researcher looking for a quick overview — this site is for you.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-4">Behind the project</h2>
      <p>
        PKD Cure Tracker is built and maintained by <a href="http://renatomolina.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Renato Molina Toth</a>, a software engineer and nutritionist based in Canada with a personal connection to the disease.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-8">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          <strong class="text-gray-700">Disclaimer:</strong> PKD Cure Tracker is for informational purposes only and does not constitute medical advice. Always consult your nephrologist or healthcare provider before making any treatment decisions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
